@startuml
autonumber
actor User
participant "Gesture Analysis" as GestureAnalysis
participant "Gesture Recognition" as GestureRecognition
participant "Face Recognition" as FaceRecognition
participant "Hand Tracking" as HandTracking
participant "Single-Hand Interaction" as SingleHandInteraction
participant "Customizable Gestures" as CustomizableGestures
participant "Real-Time Collaboration" as RealTimeCollaboration
participant "Low-Latency" as LowLatency
participant "Place-Agnostic" as PlaceAgnostic
participant "Face Detection" as FaceDetection
participant "Contour Detection" as ContourDetection
participant "Gaussian Blur" as GaussianBlur
participant "Background Subtraction" as BackgroundSubtraction
participant "Histogram Equalization" as HistogramEqualization
participant "Threading" as Threading
participant "Multiprocessing" as Multiprocessing
GestureAnalysis ->> GestureRecognition : Analyze gestures and reflect the corresponding action on the projected surface.
GestureRecognition ->> FaceRecognition : Include gesture recognition.
FaceRecognition ->> HandTracking : Include face recognition.
HandTracking ->> SingleHandInteraction : Include hand tracking.
SingleHandInteraction ->> CustomizableGestures : Include single-hand interaction.
CustomizableGestures ->> RealTimeCollaboration : Customize the actions for specific gestures.
RealTimeCollaboration ->> LowLatency : Enable real-time collaboration by supporting interactions on the projected surface.
LowLatency ->> PlaceAgnostic : Have low-latency.
FaceDetection ->> ContourDetection : Detect the user's face using the YOLOv5 model.
ContourDetection ->> GaussianBlur : Use contours detection to detect the borders of objects.
GaussianBlur ->> BackgroundSubtraction : Use Gaussian blur to mute the image noise.
BackgroundSubtraction ->> HistogramEqualization : Use Background Subtraction (BS) to separate the moving parts.
HistogramEqualization ->> Threading : Use Histogram Equalization for image contrast optimization.
Threading ->> Multiprocessing : Use threading for concurrent execution of tasks within a single process.
@enduml